Jiggly slime💫

HOW TO MAKE:
1. Add one cup of any PVA glue
2. Add in two cups of water (I actually recommend a smaller amount, maybe start with one cup)
3. Add in about 6-7 pumps of foaming hand soap
4. Add in baby oil (didn't measure exactly, but this keeps the slime from sticking to your hands so easily) 
5. Activate it (I used one teaspoon of borax with 1 cup water)
6. If there is a LOT of water like mine, take the slime out of the bowl and knead it. Once it is kneaded add more water until your desired texture
7. It may be very thick at first, let it sit overnight and it will become thinner
8. You're done! -h

Cocoa Coconut Protein Bites

Recipe:
1 scoop @growingnaturals chocolate brown rice protein powder
2 tbs powdered peanut butter
1 tsp agave 
4 tbs almond milk 
Coating:
1-2 tbs coconut flakes

Mix all ingredients in a small bowl. You might have to get your hands in there to ensure all powder mixes! Form the mixture into small bites. On a small plate measure out coconut flakes then rolls Bites in the flakes to cover. Enjoy! 
You can sub coconut flakes for cocoa nibs, nuts, seeds etc. 
Macros! One recipe has 32g Protein, 4.5g fat, and 19g carbs! Holy macros!! 👌👍💪💪

<Strawberry Milk Roll>
.
You won't believe how soft this is🍓❤
.
▪ INGREDIENTS:
-6 Egg White, 100g Sugar, 100g All-Purpose Flour, 60ml Milk, 30ml Cooking Oil, 1 tsp Vanilla Extract, 3 Tbsp Strawberry Juice
- Strawberry Cream: 100g Heavy Cream, 2 Tbsp Strawberry Juice
- Heavy Cream
.
.
▪ DIRECTIONS:
1. Make meringue by adding sugar a little at a time to egg whites. Add all-purpose flour and mix. Lastly, mix well after adding milk and cooking oil.
2. Add vanilla extract, strawberry juice and mix well.
3. Place parchment paper on a tin and pour the mixture. Flatten it out and bake in 180°C oven for 15 minutes.
4. Combine strawberry syrup with heavy cream
5. Let the sponge cake sheet chill for a while and spread half with strawberry cream and other half with heavy cream. Roll and tightly hold for 10 minutes.
.

Amerika + Mexiko = Burger-Burrito. Es wird doppelt deftig.

Dafür brauchst du (für 1 Portion):
150 g Rinderhack
Salz und Pfeffer
2 Scheiben Cheddar
1 Tortilla
1 EL Ketchup
100 g frittierte Pommes
50 g Salat, in Streifen
25 g gewürfelte Zwiebel
2 Scheiben Tomaten
2 Scheiben knusprig gebratenen Bacon

So geht es:
Würze das Hackfleisch mit Salz und Pfeffer, forme es zu einem flachen Fladen und brate ihn beidseitig an. Nach dem Wenden belegst du den Burger mit den beiden Käsescheiben. Während das Fleisch gemächlich durchgart, zerfließt der Käse.
Bestreiche den Tortilla mit Ketchup. Die Ränder bleiben dabei frei, damit der Tortilla später zusammengewickelt werden kann. Gib die Pommes auf den Ketchup, setze den fertig gebratenen Burger auf sie und streue den Salat auf ihn. Auf den Salat gibst du noch Zwiebel und Tomate. Den Abschluss bilden die Bacon-Scheiben. Nun wird der Burrito zusammengefaltet.
